    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl>Morelli in <ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>266</citedRange> (no image)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2000"/>, pp. <citedRange>43, 103</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>50.1637</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>105300</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-64474"><name nymRef="#Καλλικλῆς">Καλλικλ<supplied reason="lost">ῆς</supplied></name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Νάριστος">Ναρίσ<unclear>τ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ω</supplied></name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="2">
                        <lem resp="#cdl2000">Ναρίσ<unclear>τ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ω</supplied></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#SECir"><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-62865"><name><supplied reason="lost">Ἀ</supplied>ν<unclear>δ</unclear>ρίσ<supplied reason="lost">κω</supplied></name></persName></rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Kalliklès fils de Naristos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Kallikles son of Naristos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Kallikles figlio di Naristos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>كاليكليس بن ناريستوس</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The very fragmentary condition of the stone makes it difficult to trace its function. However the dowel hole in the upper left edge suggests that 
                it is no funerary base, but should belong to a honorary monument.</p>
	<p>The vestiges of line 2 consist in the upper half of five letters. The first one is a nu and is also the first letter of the line. The second letter might be an 
	alpha, a delta or a lambda. Rho, iota and sigma are certain. After it, a small part of a horizontal bar can only belong to a tau. Hence the proposed reading. 
	The new name <foreign xml:lang="grc">Νάριστος</foreign> is the dialectal form resulting from <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ναϝ-αριστος</foreign>, as proposed by 
	    <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2000"/></bibl>.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
